, he engages not the text but the person, the teacher, and the soul. This book is a summons to remember the testimony reduced to ashes and the voices that cry out from those ashes. Just as the teaching is embodied in the teachers, so is the tradition embodied in their portraits.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aHasidism. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848399340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438483993423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438483993/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles